Dependencies:
 * compiler that supports C++11
 * libpcap (http://www.tcpdump.org/)
 * libuuid (http://e2fsprogs.sourceforge.net/)
 * boost libraries (http://www.boost.org/)

TODO:
 * Add macros to m4/ and configure.ac:
  * https://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf-archive/ax_cxx_compile_stdcxx_11.html
    Until this macro is added, you might need to manually specify
    CXXFLAGS to enable C++11 support in your compiler. For g++,
    CXXFLAGS should include -std=gnu++11
  * https://github.com/tsuna/boost.m4

Example commands to build and run host peering:
    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure CXXFLAGS="-std=gnu++11"
    make
    ./fasguard-ad-host-peering -h
    ./fasguard-ad-host-peering -r tests/host-peering-test.pcap -o tests/output
